Package: cr
Title: Causal Regularization with and without Predefined Environments
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Francisco", "Richter", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "richtf@usi.ch"),
    person(given = c("Ernst", "C."), family = "Wit", role = "aut",
           email = "ernst.jan.camiel.wit@usi.ch"))
Description: Implements causal regularization for learning predictors that are
    robust to distribution shift, in two modes sharing the same machinery. When
    environment labels are known, ordinary causal regularization (CR) fixes the
    soft environment weights from the supplied labels and selects regularization
    strength via cross-validation. When environment labels are unknown,
    adversarial causal regularization (ACR) instead discovers the environments by
    learning soft weights adversarially (Phase 1) before the same
    cross-validation step (Phase 2). Supports linear regression, generalized
    linear models (Poisson, binomial), and generalized additive models (via
    mgcv).
